{{Infobox company | name = New English Shakespeare Company | logo = New English Shakespeare Company.png | type = | industry = Theatre | fate = | predecessor = <!-- or: | predecessors = --> | successor = <!-- or: | successors = --> | founded = <!-- if known: {{Start date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} in [[city]], state, country --> 2019 | founder = <!-- or: | founders = --> [[Jamie Hendry]] | defunct = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | hq_location_city = [[London]] | hq_location_country = | area_served = <!-- or: | areas_served = --> Worldwide | key_people = | products = | owner = <!-- or: | owners = --> | num_employees = | num_employees_year = <!-- Year of num_employees data (if known) --> | parent = | website = {{URL|nesc.org.uk}} }} '''New English Shakespeare Company''' is an English theatre company founded in 2019 by producer [[Jamie Hendry]] to present modern takes on the works of [[William Shakespeare]] on a global level.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thestage.co.uk/news/2019/jamie-hendry-sets-up-new-company-dedicated-to-touring-shakespeare-internationally/|title=Jamie Hendry sets up new company to tour Shakespeare internationally|last=Hemley|first=Matthew|date=2019-07-26|website=The Stage|language=en-US|access-date=2019-09-22}}</ref> Its inaugural production of ''[[Much Ado About Nothing]]'' was directed by [[Derek Bond (theatre director)|Derek Bond]] and opened at the [[Dubai Opera]] in September 2019 before embarking on an international tour.
== Productions ==
=== ''Much Ado About Nothing'' === ''Much Ado About Nothing'' premiered at the [[Dubai Opera]] in September 2019, directed by [[Derek Bond (theatre director)|Derek Bond]], with designs by James Perkins, lighting design by James Whiteside, music by Tayo Akinbode and movement by Lucie Pankhurst.
The production was well received with Time Out reviewing it as "Nothing short of phenomenal".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.timeoutdubai.com/culture/417174-reviewed-much-ado-about-nothing-at-dubai-opera|title=Reviewed: Much Ado About Nothing at Dubai Opera|date=2019-09-26|website=Time Out Dubai|language=en|access-date=2019-10-08}}</ref> {| class="wikitable mw-collapsible" |+2019 Original Cast !Role !Actor |- |Ursula |Geri Allen |- |Leonato |James Clyde |- |Don John / Dogberry |Samuel Collings |- |Benedick |Simon Darwen |- |Beatrice |Kirsten Foster |- |Hero |Adele James |- |Balthasar / Verges / Friar |William Pennington |- |Claudio |Daniel Reid-Walters |- |Borachio |Adam Sopp |- |Don Pedro |Obioma Ugoala |- |Margaret |Zoe West |}
